  "texts": [
    "Section 1: Understanding generative AI: exploring its forms, techniques, and usesGenerative AI is an entity that utilizes deep learning models to produce human-like content such as text, audio, images, or other data types in response to diverse and complex prompts (such as instructions, languages or questions) [12].",
    "Generative AI stands out from conversational AI by its ability to generate not just responses, but entirely new and original content at a larger scale [12,13].",
    "Generative AI, like AI, is a collective term for a variety of algorithmic techniques [13,14].",
    "Although generative AI has been around for a decade now, the emergence of ChatGPT inspired a new era of innovation and research in the field of artificial intelligence.",
    "This upsurge has resulted in the development and implementation of various cutting-edge tools, including Gemini (Google AI), GPT-4 (Open AI), Stable Diffusion, DALL-E, StyleGAN, and WaveNet, among many [15][16][17][18][19]."
